  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The computational model targets absolute hemolysis index prediction for a Class III VAD at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; seven factors were evaluated against required gradation levels and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. The intended use scope — regulatory submission supporting 510(k) substantial-equivalence argument for a Class III implantable VAD in adults with end-stage heart failure, operating at 3–6 L/min flow and 2000–3500 RPM — is described in the Claim and Requirement prose but is not linked via a structured hasContextOfUse node, consistent with the Minimal profile declaration.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-prediction-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
